      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. they made it to the final round for a senior dev position but we decided to go with someone else. can you draft something professional and polite?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here are a few options for a professional and polite rejection email for your final-round candidate. Remember to keep the tone respectful, even if the decision was tough. It's a delicate situation, so you want to maintain a positive relationship with them, even if they weren't the chosen one.\n\nHere is a draft you can adapt:\n\nSubject: Update on the Senior Developer Position at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us for the Senior Developer position. We truly enjoyed getting to know you and learning more about your impressive experience. The final round was incredibly competitive, and we were genuinely impressed by your skills. At this stage, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific background was a slightly closer match to the immediate needs of this particular role.\n\nWe sincerely appreciate the time and effort you invested in this process, and we wish you the very best in your job search and future endeavors. Please keep in touch!\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n\n***\n\n*Self-Correction/Refinement:* You might want to add a sentence about keeping their resume on file, depending on your company policy. If you do, keep it",
